    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "The part most people will miss from this paper:\n\nDevelopers who delegated everything to AI scored below 40%. But developers who used AI to ask conceptual questions and understand the code scored above 65%.\n\nSame tool. Completely different outcomes.\n\nThe problem isn’t AI coding.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2030799882953376219",
    "time": "2026-03-09 08:16",
    "id_str": "2030799882953376219",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "Here’s the cycle that traps you. \n\nAI speeds up a task → expectations for speed rise → you rely more on AI → you take on wider scope → workload intensifies → repeat",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2030819414614868225",
    "time": "2026-03-09 09:34",
    "id_str": "2030819414614868225",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
